@node run " User Msg v3.6 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also, which should already be done.

 Move the "User_Msg" directory into  the "gremlins" dir & run the door via
 a BBS menu using MAXs Function 34, eg: "gremlins:user_msg/user_msg".  The
 other door is run during the login sequence so you need to place the door
 in the "introdoor.text", eg: gremlins/user_msg/user_msg-view".

 To access the SysOp's Menu, press ALT-SHIFT-S and away you go.  Those who
 can  access  this menu have their name placed in the "User_Msg.axs" file.

 To lock out unwanted users,  place their name in "User_Msg.lockout" file.

 The file "User_Msg.txt" is created when a user leaves a msg and the other
 file, "User_Msg.txt2" is created when the SysOp leaves a msg.

 Any probs, etc.. @{"contact" link call} me.

@endnode
